      Indicates if the annotation is active; inactive annotations are ignored by all system processes (Boolean).
      is_in_agreement
      Reserved.
      is_negated
      Negation flag for the annotation; when true
      for assignments, indicates that the annotation is a negative example (i.e., known to not be an example of the Label)
      for judgments, indicates that the judgment rejects the original assignment, referenced by the subject_id
      (Boolean).
      is_trainable
      Indicates the annotation has reached a confidence / judgment threshold sufficient to be used for training (Boolean).
      label

      Reserved.
      provenance
      The provenance (creator class) of this annotation (String, but must be one of the provenance enumerant values Annotation.Provenance).
      queued_at
      Reserved.
      requested_for
      Reserved.
      status
      The current status of this annotation; updated by the system as- needed based on machine learning optimizations (String).
      subject_id
      Judgments-only The UUID of the assignment which this annotation is judging (UUID String).
      task
      Assignments-only The task annotated by this annotation (JsonObject with a single name key).
      text
      Span annotations-only The text inside the span (String).
      text2
      Free-form text about this annotation; often used to store a human- readable reason why the annotation was created (String, max 255 characters.
      updated_at
      Date the annotation was most recently updated (ISO-8601 String).
      user_id
      The UUID of the user who created this annotation, if the annotation was created by a known user (UUID String).
      uuid
      This annotation's UUID (UUID String).
